        <hr class="h2-line">
        <h2>Here's a list of Quincy Larson's achievments with freeCodeCamp.org:</h2>
          <ul id="tribute-info">
            <li>Quincy Larson was a school director for six years before he started to learn to code, so that he could create tools for making schools more efficient.
            </li>
            <li>After graduate school, he created freeCodeCamp as a way to streamline a student's progress from beginner to being job-ready.
            </li>
            <li>freeCodeCamp was offically launched in October 2014 and incorporated as Free Code Camp, Inc.
            </li>
            <li>The self-paced curriculum involves 1,400 hours of interactive coding challenges and web development projects.
            </li>
            <li>freeCodeCamp's platform is used by about 350,000 unique visitors per month, with students from over 160 countries.
            </li>
            <li>In 2016, freeCodeCamp announced their "Open Source for Good" initiative, which extends and open sources their nonprofit work to all nonprofits and organizations to use.
            </li>
            <li>Many languages, technologies, and courses currently taught by freeCodeCamp, you can view the full curriculum and <a id="curriculum-link" target="_blank" href="https://www.freecodecamp.org/learn/" >learn more here</a>.
            </li>
          </ul>
        <hr class="section-line">
        <section>If you have time read more about about this incredible open souce community on their <a id="tribute-link" target="_blank" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/FreeCodeCamp"> Wikipedia page</a>
        </section>
